Avian chlamydiosis, French Polynesia
------------------------------------
Information received on 10 Oct 2013 from Dr Valerie Roy, [Head, Department of Food Quality and Veterinary Action, Rural Development Service, Ministry of Agriculture, Livestock and Forestry], Papeete, French Polynesia

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 13 Mar 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 17 Jul 2013
Report date: 9 Oct 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 10 Oct 2013
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: _Chlamydophila psittaci_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1: Sanitary landfill, Paihoro (Taravao), Taiarapu-Est, Tahiti, [Windward Islands]
Date of start of the outbreak: 13 Mar 2013
Outbreak status: resolved (3 Oct 2013)
Epidemiological unit: not applicable
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Rock pigeon (rock dove): _Columba livia_ (Columbidae) / 30 / 5 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected animals: wild rock pigeons (_Columba livia_) feeding on the sanitary landfill of Tahiti.

Outbreak 2: Coastal area, Paea, Paea, Tahiti, [Windward Islands]
Date of start of the outbreak: 22 May 2013
Outbreak status: Resolved (3 Oct 2013)
Epidemiological unit: Not applicable
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Rock pigeon (rock dove): _Columba livia_ (Columbidae) / 10 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected animals: wild rock pigeons (_Columba livia_) collected in the coastal area of Paea.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Rock pigeon (rock dove): _Columba livia_ (Columbidae) / 40 / 6 / 0 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost (removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter)
Rock pigeon (rock dove): _Columba livia_ (Columbidae) / 15 percent / 0 percent / 0 percent / 0 percent

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: an investigation was carried out on the presence of OIE avian diseases in Tahiti in the avifauna in 4 wild bird species (365 animals sampled): rock pigeon (_Columba livia_), common myna (_Acridotheres tristis_), red-vented bulbul (_Pycnonotus cafer_), and zebra dove (_Geopelia striata_). The presence of _Chlamydophila psittaci_ has been only detected in rock pigeons in 2 locations -- in the sanitary landfill in Paihoro and in the coastal area of Paea. Shipment of Columbidae, Psittacidae, and Anatidae from Tahiti towards the other islands has been suspended.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; zoning; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

